    Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

The vendored sources are placed under client-android/app/ by vendor-kai.sh and
retain their original Apache-2.0 license and per-file headers. A copy of the
upstream license ships inside the vendored tree (app/LICENSE or app/LICENSE.txt),
and VENDOR.txt records the exact commit that was vendored.

Modifications made by the Deneb project (removing non-Android targets, removing
Kai's brain/data layer, and wiring the UI to the Deneb gateway) are described in
README.md and are likewise licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
